    "We used the Mann-Whitney U test because our samples were still independent.",
    "The distribution for our two samples was normal (Shapiro-Wilk = 0.901, p = 0.256 for GPT-generated complaints, and Shapiro-Wilk = 0.850, p = 0.074 for lawyer-generated ones).",
    "The variances for both of our samples were the same.",
    "Federal courts have jurisdiction over violations of federal law (Practical Law 2023).",
    "Federal Courts can also exercise diversity jurisdiction where the amount in controversy exceeds $5 million and on the basis of geographic diversity between plaintiffs and defendants (Lender et al. 2023)."
